IS
A
COMMONLY
AND
GENERALLY
BENIGN
REACTION
THAT
OCCURS
IN
MANY
PATHOPHYSIOLOGIC
STATES
STEATOSIS
CAN
RESULT
FROM
THE
FOLLOWING
MECHANISMS
IMPAIRED
TGC
CLEARANCE
INCREASED
HEPATIC
LIPOGENESIS
DECREASED
FA
OXIDATION
AND
INCREASED
LIPOLYSIS
CYSTIC
FIBROSIS
AND
SYNDROMES
PRODUCING
PANCREATIC
INSUFFICIENCY
PANCREATITIS
RESULT
IN
A
VARIABLE
DEGREE
OF
STEATOSIS
MOST
PROBABLY
DEPENDENT
ON
THE
NUTRITIONAL
AND
